obo:ECO_0001230  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_211  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Quantitative mass spectrometry and immunoblotting of highly purified synaptic vesicles from the rat brain indicate that Rab6a copurifies with synaptic vesicles.\n\nThe SV/homogenate enrichment ratios of Rab6A and 6B are 1.68 (WB) and 2.59 and 3.37 (iTRAQ), respectively in the Pavlos paper. However, no co-localisation of either rabs with synaptophysin puncta was observed (Table 1). I used the term co-purify rather than enrichment to more strictly distinguish if a protein is just present in a biochemical fractionation versus if additional evidence is available to support that it is also spatially present or enriched in the SVs by microscopic methods.. Experimental description: Legend to Figure 2 \"Enrichment profiles of Rab GTPases on purified SVs isolated from rat brain homogenates, determined by quantitative immunoblotting\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_211" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

